I learned something in 2023 that was v hard for me to swallow.

Ethereum never really banked the unbanked. Neither did bitcoin or solana. They are too volatile, too expensive, or too new.

It was tron that banked the unbanked around the world.

Most stablecoin activities across emerging economies happen on tron usdt. You can see this in the onchain data, or by talking to ppl in those countries.

Tron benefited from a massive first mover advantage. It was one of the first fast cheap chains. It was one of the first chains that supported usdt. And it was one of the first chains supported by binance which created an enormous distribution channel.

In hindsight, tron‚Äôs success in those countries was not a coincidence.

You may be shocked, incredulous, or disgusted. But I‚Äôll use this example to constantly remind myself to stay intellectually honest and flexible.
